content.rendered:
You need to know the current NFR Tie-Down Roping WEATHER GUARD® PRCA 2021 World Standings (Tie-Down Roping) – in accordance with the money won during the regular season, the Justin Boots Playoffs and Championships, and for many bull riders, the PRCA Xtreme Bulls Tour.

Watch NFR 2023 Live Online - SUBSCRIBE HERE

NFR 2023 Streaming info
Streaming
The Cowboy Channel (real-time) Watch Here
RFD-TV (real-time) Watch Here
Cowboy Channel Plus (International) Watch Here

 

Tie-Down Roping has one of the highest gaps in the ProRodeo when it comes to the first and second positions. On the top, we have 20-year old Shad Mayfield with more than $90,000 to the second-placed Tuf Cooper.

There will be a lot of competition from other contestants if they want to match or even be close to Mayfield earnings for the season. The 2019 World Champion Haven Meged is placed third, and the new No.4 is Tyler Milligan after he finished second at the Gold Buckle Beer ProRodeo Tour Finale.

Milligan was beaten by Tyson Durfey, who is the 2016 World Champion. The ProRodeo Tour Finale win pushed Durfey from position No.20 to no.12.
